Interface MenuInterface

All Known Implementing Classes:
MainMenu
public interface MenuInterface
Interface defining contract for menu operations. Demonstrates Abstraction and Polymorphism OOP principles. This interface ensures all menu implementations provide consistent functionality while allowing different implementations.
Author:
Student - Software Maintenance Course

  • Method Details

    • showMenu

      void showMenu()
      Show the menu to the user. Demonstrates Abstraction - defines what should happen without specifying implementation details.

    • hideMenu

      void hideMenu()
      Hide the menu from view. Each implementing class can hide menus differently.

    • cleanup

      void cleanup()
      Clean up menu resources. Important for proper resource management.

    • isMenuReady

      default boolean isMenuReady()
      Default method (Java 8+ feature) providing common functionality. Demonstrates how interfaces can provide default implementations while still maintaining the contract.
      Returns:
      true if menu is ready to display
